SUMMARY:Next Level Workshop  Discovering the Unexpected
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Move beyond your preconceptions into a state of authentic disc
 overy with collaborative masters Carol Mickett and Robert Stackhouse. Thro
 ugh a deliberately limited palette of materials\, you will engage in creat
 ing 48 quick artworks. This is not about perfection its about letting go o
 f control to uncover surprising moments of interest and meaning. Guided cr
 itiques throughout will help you recognize patterns\, break habits\, and r
 eframe your relationship to your own work. You will select one or two of y
 our 48 pieces to develop further. Leave with new work and renewed confiden
 ce in where the unexpected can lead! Ages 18  All Levels  All Supplies and
  lunch included. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/185956
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185956
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2c7b2884-bef8-41b0-b984-fb90e274ef56
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260303T000728Z
DTSTART:20260411T140000Z
DTEND:20260411T153000Z
SUMMARY:Walking Tour: Downtown Tampa
LOCATION:400 N. Franklin St. Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a unique activity to do in Tampa Bay? Join the Tam
 pa Bay History Center for an immersive downtown walking tour. This guided 
 trek leads you past some of the citys most storied landmarks\, including C
 ity Hall\, Sacred Heart Church\, the Floridan Palace Hotel\, and The Hub\,
  Tampas oldest bar. Along the route\, your guide will share the stories th
 at connect these sites to the citys vibrant past. The tour lasts 90 minute
 s\, begins at 10 a.m.\, and is limited to 25 guests for a more personal ex
 perience. The route covers about one mile along sidewalks and brick street
 s\, so comfortable shoes and outdoor attire are recommended. Your starting
  point is Lykes Gaslight Park at 400 N. Franklin St.\, right in the center
  of downtown. Street parking is available nearby\, making it easy to begin
  your journey. Advance tickets are required\, and private tours can be boo
 ked by calling (813) 228-0097. Group size is small and tickets go fast. Re
 serve your spot today and experience downtown Tampa through the lens of hi
 story. Looking for other tours? Visit our walking tour page . \n\nPermalin
 k: https://www.tampa.gov/node/185851
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185851
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6a993e5b-cded-40aa-bd1e-622d9bd7ebf2
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260303T000728Z
DTSTART:20260411T120000Z
DTEND:20260411T160000Z
SUMMARY:Walk For Wishes Tampa
LOCATION:1701 N Highland Ave Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:The 13th Annual Walk for Wishes Tampa will take place on Satur
 day\, April 11\, 2026. Lace up your shoes and join us for a heartwarming d
 ay of fitness and fun at Water Works Park! For additional event details\, 
 please visit walkforwishestampa.org. Walk For Wishes is a feel-good event 
 that everyone from student groups to large companies can participate in an
 d make a difference in the lives of local children and families. Since the
